cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NA, cs.MS, cs.DS

Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the mutual information of a multiple antenna radio transmission channel. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the analysis of a self-adjoint operator and the behavior of the Stieltjes transform, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.SI (Systems and Control) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of the Hilbert space and the IDS may also indicate a connection to cs.MS (Mathematical Software) or cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics).
